Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.25,0:00:08.19,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Just one more time.{\i0}\N{\i1}Please!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.95,0:00:11.12,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, but this\Nis the last one.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:12.72,0:00:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoo hoo!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.93,0:00:15.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Wheeeee!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.18,0:00:22.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh dear me!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.34,0:00:25.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure wish you'd come\Nswimmin' with us, Granny.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.45,0:00:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, dear, but I just\Ncan't bring myself anywhere
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.99,0:00:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,near that there\Nswimmin' hole.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.18,0:00:32.99,Default,,0,0,0,,How come?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.65,0:00:36.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I wasn't\Nalways this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.60,0:00:43.96,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Time was, I was an{\i0}\N{\i1}aqua-pony all star.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:45.81,0:00:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}In fact, I was the only{\i0}\N{\i1}Apple to ever come close{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.72,0:00:51.60,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}to breaking the Equestria{\i0}\N{\i1}high diving record.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.03,0:00:58.81,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Falling six stories into{\i0}\N{\i1}a deep-dish pie pan{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.83,0:01:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}takes a toll on{\i0}\N{\i1}the hindquarters.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.44,0:01:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I was so sore,\Nit took years
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.48,0:01:06.17,Default,,0,0,0,,before I could even\Nlook at the water again.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.44,0:01:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Just the idea of swimming\Nmakes my whole body ache.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.91,0:01:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, these old legs can't\Neven paddle fast enough
Dialogue: 0,0:01:14.11,0:01:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,to stay afloat.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.22,0:01:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Boy, I sure would hate\Nto be afraid of swimming.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.31,0:01:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think I'll ever\Nbe scared of the water?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.35,0:01:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Aaah!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.10,0:01:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Nnope.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.06,0:01:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Subtitles by YayPonies\Nhttp://yayponies.eu{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:14.44,0:02:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Wow, Granny.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.88,0:02:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't believe you\Nwere a high diver.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.22,0:02:20.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The best one in Ponyville.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.94,0:02:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you think I could\Nbe a high diver?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.24,0:02:23.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Nnope.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.04,0:02:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Absolutely not!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.43,0:02:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.82,0:02:28.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you hold your horse\Nfeathers, little seed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:28.81,0:02:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I never said being a high\Ndiver was a smart decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.32,0:02:34.12,Default,,0,0,0,,It's incredibly dangerous.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.27,0:02:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I know, but--
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.08,0:02:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,But nothin'!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.22,0:02:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It is the riskiest, scariest,\Ndarned fool thing I ever did do.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:40.52,0:02:43.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That's not to say I don't wish\NI was still young and spry
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.52,0:02:45.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and confident, but\Nlet's leave the flying
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.88,0:02:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,through the air to the pegasi.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.75,0:02:52.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow, when you put it that\Nway, it doesn't sound so fun.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.87,0:03:01.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Wow. I wonder where\Neverypony's heading.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.60,0:03:13.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, where in Ponyville do\Nyou two think you're going?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.14,0:03:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, quit being such a worry\Nworm and follow your ears.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.01,0:03:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, Applejack.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.38,0:03:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Aren't you curious?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.34,0:03:43.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Shhh!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.58,0:03:54.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you one and all for your\Nattendance and we guarantee that
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.51,0:03:56.61,Default,,0,0,0,,your time here will\Nnot be spent in vain.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.61,0:03:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, we think it will prove\Nto be the most valuable time
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.31,0:04:00.45,Default,,0,0,0,,you've ever spent.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.49,0:04:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The Flim Flam Brothers!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.05,0:04:04.81,Default,,0,0,0,,This should be interesting.\NEeyup
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.05,0:04:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome one and all to the\Ndemonstration of a lifetime.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.90,0:04:09.80,Default,,0,0,0,,A demonstration\Nof a better life.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.82,0:04:11.98,Default,,0,0,0,,A demonstration\Nof a better time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.98,0:04:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And if we haven't captured\Nyour interest just yet,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.29,0:04:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,by the time we finish an\Nunfortunate phenomenon
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.89,0:04:18.58,Default,,0,0,0,,practically guarantees\Nthat we will.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.63,0:04:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,A phenomenon?\NWhat's that?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.35,0:04:22.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a circumstance\Nperceptible by the senses,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.75,0:04:25.18,Default,,0,0,0,,but in this case it's\Nthe simple fact that...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.53,0:04:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ There's ailments{\i0}\N{\i1}all around us, ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.09,0:04:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ in everything we{\i0}\N{\i1}touch and see. ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.28,0:04:31.22,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ The sickness that{\i0}\N{\i1}lies waiting there, ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.22,0:04:33.04,Default,,0,0,0,,♪ in every breath you breathe.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.10,0:04:36.75,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ Disease will up and grab you{\i0}\N{\i1}as it crawls from land and sea ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.86,0:04:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ It's amazing how infected{\i0}\N{\i1}that the natural world ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.73,0:04:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ and all its things can be. {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.90,0:04:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I understand that some of\Nyou don't think you're sick
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.85,0:04:47.18,Default,,0,0,0,,but twisted hooves\Nand aching joints
Dialogue: 0,0:04:47.19,0:04:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,don't heal all that quick.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.83,0:04:52.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Consider just how dangerous\Nthis world is, you might-
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.13,0:04:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,♪ Slip and fall, break or sprain\N{\i1}something here tonight ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.51,0:04:59.09,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ But luckily for you we've{\i0}\N{\i1}got the thing you need. ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.54,0:05:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ And it's easier when{\i0}\N{\i1}all you need's the cure ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.31,0:05:06.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ The Flim Flam Miracle{\i0}\N{\i1}Curative Tonic ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.91,0:05:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ Is just what the{\i0}\N{\i1}doctor ordered, I'm sure. ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.76,0:05:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I know our claims\Nseem fantastical...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.77,0:05:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,impractical,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:12.73,0:05:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,improbable,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.62,0:05:14.80,Default,,0,0,0,,impossible...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.83,0:05:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And magical!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.45,0:05:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So we welcome every\Nsuffering pony
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.75,0:05:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to make their way\Nup to the stage.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.32,0:05:21.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Now don't crowd.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.46,0:05:23.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And we'll prove our\Ntonic's effectiveness
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.46,0:05:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,before your very eyes!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.84,0:05:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,You there! Come\Nup here, good sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.40,0:05:30.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll wager you're tired of\Nthose crutches, my friend.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.16,0:05:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Try taking a sip of this!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.86,0:05:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,♪ That's why you're so lucky!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.82,0:05:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,♪ We've got the thing for you
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.17,0:05:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ Just come on up, we've{\i0}\N{\i1}always got some more! ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.94,0:06:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ of the Flim Flam Miracle{\i0}\N{\i1}Curative Tonic ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.64,0:06:03.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ I won't need these crutches{\i0}\N{\i1}to dance out the door! ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.23,0:06:05.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, how do you like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.08,0:06:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.11,0:06:09.73,Default,,0,0,0,,There's something funny\Nabout this whole thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.77,0:06:16.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ Now some of you may suffer{\i0}\N{\i1}from feelings of despair ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.43,0:06:18.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ You're old, you're tired,{\i0}\N{\i1}your legs won't work ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.56,0:06:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,♪ There's greying in your hair
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.68,0:06:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ Just listen; I'll tell you{\i0}\N{\i1}that you don't need to fear ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.97,0:06:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ Your ears will work,{\i0}\N{\i1}your muscles tone ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.84,0:06:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,♪ Your eyes will see so clear!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.92,0:06:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ Luckily for us you've{\i0}\N{\i1}got the thing we need! ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.53,0:06:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ The answer to our{\i0}\N{\i1}problems in a jar ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.29,0:06:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ The Flim Flam Miracle{\i0}\N{\i1}Curative Tonic ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.05,0:06:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ It's the greatest ever{\i0}\N{\i1}miracle by far! ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.76,0:06:46.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}It cures the Reins, the{\i0}\N{\i1}spurs and clydesdale fur blight{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.39,0:06:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Hooferia and horsyntary,\Ncured in just a night!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.48,0:06:51.64,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You've got swollen{\i0}\N{\i1}hooves and hindquarters{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.65,0:06:53.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}or terrible bridle bit cleft.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.25,0:06:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Saunter sits and gallop plop,{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.06,0:06:56.77,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}or give your tail some heft.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.86,0:07:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Mane loss, Hay Fever,{\i0}\N{\i1}or terrible tonsillitis.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.17,0:07:02.74,Default,,0,0,0,,You heard it here folks, this\Nis the only place in all of
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.75,0:07:04.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Equestria you'll find it.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:04.82,0:07:08.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ It can make you short or{\i0}\N{\i1}tall or even grow old. ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.42,0:07:10.27,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ But who'd want that?{\i0}\N{\i1}When with one drink, ♪{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.49,0:07:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}♪ you can be young again... {\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.29,0:07:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,SOLD!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.63,0:07:16.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Congratulations, Granny Smith.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.65,0:07:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}You've just made the{\i0}\N{\i1}purchase of a lifetime!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.89,0:07:22.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you as\Nworried as I am?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.81,0:07:23.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Eeyup.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.29,0:07:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah! I just can't\Nbelieve all the things
Dialogue: 0,0:07:35.08,0:07:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,that Flim Flam tonic can do.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.68,0:07:40.51,Default,,0,0,0,,When somepony says something's\Ntoo good to be true,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.86,0:07:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,it usually is.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.38,0:07:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,You mean Granny\Nwasted her money?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.87,0:07:48.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I don't know about that,\Nbut I don't think there's a
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.76,0:07:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,tonic in Equestria that can\Nmake an old pony young again.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.98,0:07:53.90,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Howdeee!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.79,0:07:58.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Granny?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.33,0:08:02.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Hang on now! We'll get you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.00,0:08:26.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Granny, I thought you were too\Nafraid of the water to swim!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.38,0:08:28.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And what about your hip?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.52,0:08:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I reckon it might have\Nbeen a problem before I had
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.53,0:08:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,myself a dose of that\Nthere Flim Flam Tonic.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:34.72,0:08:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm not so sure that tonic\Nreally does anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.79,0:08:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't do anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.50,0:08:40.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you call this?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.61,0:08:51.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm glad you're\Nfeeling good,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.32,0:08:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,but how do you know\Nit's from the tonic?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.21,0:08:56.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I looked out at\Nthe water this morning
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.68,0:09:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and I felt the same terrifying\Naches and pains I always do,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.81,0:09:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,but one sip of that magic\Nelixir and it all went away.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.41,0:09:08.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, I might even get a\Nhead start on my chores.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.43,0:09:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you say, Big Macadoo?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.24,0:09:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Up for a little\Nafternoon apple bucking?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.16,0:09:14.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh, Nnope.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.99,0:09:17.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Aw, quit yer belly aching!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:18.12,0:09:21.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Gee, it looks like that\Ntonic works after all.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.30,0:09:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I wonder what's in it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.81,0:09:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I think maybe it's\Ntime we found out.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.18,0:09:33.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you're just gonna walk\Nup and ask them how it works?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.08,0:09:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess, though if\Nit's a genuine cure,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.78,0:09:39.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't suppose they'll be too\Nkeen on sharing the recipe.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.41,0:09:46.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait a second!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.34,0:09:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,That's that same\Npony from before!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.05,0:09:52.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.38,0:10:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Now hold it right there, Mr...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.24,0:10:04.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Sh-sh-Shill.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.81,0:10:05.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Silver Shill.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.22,0:10:09.41,Default,,0,0,0,,W-w-what do you two want?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:09.86,0:10:12.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Our Granny took some tonic and\Nwe want to know how it works.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.16,0:10:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Granny couldn't swim\Nbefore and now she can.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.99,0:10:18.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Just like you couldn't\Nwalk and now you can.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.20,0:10:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But what are you\Ndoing back here?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.30,0:10:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, if the tonic\Ncured you and all?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.00,0:10:32.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Because he's part of the act.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.27,0:10:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,It's time for you\Nto tell the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.04,0:10:38.47,Default,,0,0,0,,You never needed\Ncrutches at all, did you?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.94,0:10:40.06,Default,,0,0,0,,I... uh.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.27,0:10:43.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.49,0:10:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.74,0:10:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if it isn't our\Nmost favorite Apple!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.35,0:11:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,What brings you back\Nto our humble abode?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.17,0:11:06.12,Default,,0,0,0,,You two charlatans sold my\NGranny a bottle of tonic
Dialogue: 0,0:11:06.27,0:11:08.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and now she's off acting\Nlike a filly again.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.54,0:11:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,What's so bad about that?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.50,0:11:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,If she keeps gallivanting\Naround like a yearling,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.70,0:11:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,she's apt to drop from\Nexhaustion or worse.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.44,0:11:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,What's more, I know for a\Nfact that your friend here
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.51,0:11:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,is dressing up as a\Ndifferent pony every night
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.59,0:11:23.40,Default,,0,0,0,,so he can pretend to be cured.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.01,0:11:26.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's quite\Nan accusation.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.41,0:11:27.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But let's say\Nthat it's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.55,0:11:29.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Hypothetically.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.48,0:11:30.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Theoretically.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.43,0:11:33.29,Default,,0,0,0,,As I understand, your Granny\Nwas a famous aqua-pony...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.31,0:11:35.72,Default,,0,0,0,,The star of the show,\Nonce upon a time...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.09,0:11:38.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But hasn't set so much as\Na hoof in the water since.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.46,0:11:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Until today.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.62,0:11:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:41.37,0:11:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, then even if our tonic\Nwere nothing more than a mixture
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.04,0:11:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,of apple juice\Nand beet leaves...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.61,0:11:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Hypothetically.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.71,0:11:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Theoretically.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.92,0:11:52.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact is that\NGranny is happier now
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.99,0:11:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,than before she tried it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.64,0:11:55.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I guess.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.96,0:11:57.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the question is...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.73,0:11:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you really want\Nto be the pony
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.49,0:12:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,who takes all that\Nhappiness away?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.52,0:12:05.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.80,0:12:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,There you are!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.05,0:12:08.41,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been looking\Nall over.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.54,0:12:10.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you find out\Nwhat's in the tonic?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.41,0:12:17.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Honestly, Apple Bloom,\Nas long as it works,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.90,0:12:20.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't suppose\Nit really matters.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.98,0:12:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, if it doesn't\Nmatter to you,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.88,0:12:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,then it doesn't matter\Nto me either, sis.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.38,0:12:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the spirit!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.96,0:12:32.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Come back anytime!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.92,0:12:38.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey Granny, think you can\Nbuck me over the water?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.59,0:12:40.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't see why not.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.48,0:12:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, Big Mac,\Ntoss her this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.40,0:12:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Granny, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.16,0:12:46.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoo hoo hoo!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.61,0:12:51.66,Default,,0,0,0,,What were you saying, dear?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.45,0:12:55.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Granny, don't you think you\Nshould take it kinda easy?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.70,0:12:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been taking it\Neasy for too long
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.23,0:13:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and now, thanks to that Flim\NFlam tonic, I don't have to.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.15,0:13:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Granny, do you think I could\Nbe an aqua-pony like you?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.24,0:13:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course you can, sapling.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.41,0:13:09.38,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}There's nothing to{\i0}\N{\i1}it but to do it.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.29,0:13:12.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the Ponyville\Nswim meet is coming up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.94,0:13:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,We could enter together.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.24,0:13:16.51,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}A legendary water{\i0}\N{\i1}pony like you?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.77,0:13:18.12,Default,,0,0,0,,We'd be a cinch to win.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.80,0:13:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmmm. I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.74,0:13:23.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Being back in the\Nwater is one thing,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.89,0:13:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,but a competition is a\Npony of a different color.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:27.69,0:13:29.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. OK.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.38,0:13:34.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know, Granny.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.68,0:13:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,A swim meet sounds pretty safe.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.76,0:13:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And after all, if that tonic\Nlets you swim in a river
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.63,0:13:42.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and a swimming hole, a pool\Nshould be no problem at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.20,0:13:45.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'll be a tart\Nturnover, you are right!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.20,0:13:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,All we need now is\Nmore tonic!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.18,0:13:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome friends\Nand step right up!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.06,0:13:57.33,Default,,0,0,0,,The next show starts\Nin five minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.54,0:14:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,But why not buy your tonic\Nnow and avoid the rush?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.75,0:14:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Right this way,\Ngood sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.06,0:14:04.59,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}We'll take the{\i0}\N{\i1}whole case!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.35,0:14:12.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you saying this\Nstuff actually works?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.34,0:14:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It seems to work for Granny.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.19,0:14:19.21,Default,,0,0,0,,You heard it here first, folks.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.37,0:14:22.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Flim Flam Miracle Curative\NTonic is Granny Smith tested
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.76,0:14:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and Applejack approved!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.30,0:14:29.54,Default,,0,0,0,,If Applejack says it works,\Nthat's good enough for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:54.06,0:14:57.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Hoo ha hee hee! Ha hoo ha!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.97,0:15:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Just remember you two,\Nthe most important thing
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.43,0:15:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,is to be safe and have\Nfun. Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.88,0:15:04.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Fiddlesticks!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.75,0:15:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,With the routine we've\Nbeen working on,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.52,0:15:09.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll be a plum pudding if\Nwe don't win this thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:11.12,0:15:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.05,0:15:12.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Good luck, then.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.25,0:15:13.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Luck?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.69,0:15:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Who needs luck?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.75,0:15:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got tonic on our side.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.98,0:15:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Flim Flam's Magical{\i0}\N{\i1}Curative Tonic!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.05,0:15:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Get your Applejack\Napproved tonic!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.00,0:15:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Granny Smith drinks\Nit, why shouldn't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.95,0:15:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.75,0:15:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Now if you'll excuse us,\N{\i1}we've got some swimming to do.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.83,0:16:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'll be.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.79,0:16:26.51,Default,,0,0,0,,That was some of the most\Namazing aqua-batics
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.57,0:16:27.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I've ever seen.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.44,0:16:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,How in Equestria did you do it?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.34,0:16:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Hard work? Lots of practice?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.81,0:16:34.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but mostly it's the tonic.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:34.48,0:16:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,That's Flim Flam's Miracle\NCurative Tonic, to be precise.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.24,0:16:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Buy it now, while\Nsupplies last.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.66,0:16:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you\Ndoing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.16,0:16:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Things are going so well, Flim\Nand Flam gave me a promotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.50,0:16:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Just made my first\Nbit as a salespony.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.84,0:17:03.11,Default,,0,0,0,,No more costumes\Nfor this pony.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.10,0:17:07.12,Default,,0,0,0,,This is more of\Na uniform.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.12,0:17:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,If you say so.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.03,0:17:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I used to wonder if I was\Ndoing the right thing, you know
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.80,0:17:14.09,Default,,0,0,0,,pretending to be cured,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.12,0:17:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,basically lying to\Nfolks about this tonic,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.69,0:17:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,but thanks to you, I realized
Dialogue: 0,0:17:18.94,0:17:21.86,Default,,0,0,0,,that sometimes honesty\Nisn't the best policy.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.33,0:17:22.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks to...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.17,0:17:23.80,Default,,0,0,0,,me?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.47,0:17:27.30,Default,,0,0,0,,With Film Flam's\NMagical Curative Tonic,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:27.42,0:17:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,my Granny can do anything!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.40,0:17:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Just ask Applejack.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.48,0:17:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,No! This has gotta stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.97,0:17:40.87,Default,,0,0,0,,If ponies keep believing that\Ntonic can do things it can't,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.12,0:17:42.58,Default,,0,0,0,,who knows what will happen?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.18,0:17:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe something\Nlike that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.49,0:17:51.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Granny!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.10,0:17:56.38,Default,,0,0,0,,What in blazes does\Nshe think she's doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.68,0:17:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Granny's going to break the\NEquestria high diving record.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.84,0:18:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Land sakes!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.90,0:18:31.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, what in tarnation\Ndid you do that for?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.73,0:18:34.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the most\Nfool-pony thing
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.57,0:18:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I've ever seen anypony\Ndo in all my life.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.35,0:18:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't do a dive like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.38,0:18:43.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Aw, quit your fussin'.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.29,0:18:46.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I had enough tonic to do\Na dive ten times as high.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.90,0:18:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Twenty times by\Nmy count.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.67,0:18:50.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Thirty with a\Nfavorable breeze.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.01,0:19:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate to disappoint\Neverypony,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.93,0:19:06.16,Default,,0,0,0,,but there's no way Granny\Ncould have made that dive
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.18,0:19:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,because this\Ntonic is a fake.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.37,0:19:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But you gave it your\Nstamp of approval!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.67,0:19:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you saying you lied?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.81,0:19:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.30,0:19:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't mean to.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.57,0:19:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But everypony seemed\Nso much happier,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.97,0:19:24.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}I couldn't bring{\i0}\N{\i1}myself to tell you{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.36,0:19:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}when I found out the{\i0}\N{\i1}tonic wasn't real.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.43,0:19:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I know it was wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.98,0:19:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I just hope, with time, I can\Nwin back everypony's trust.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.37,0:19:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But if the tonic is a fake then\Nhow come Granny can swim again
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.13,0:19:41.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and what about all that\Naqua-batic stuff we just did?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.20,0:19:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I reckon sometimes you can\Nforget what you're capable of
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.31,0:19:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and it just takes a little\Nextra confidence to remember
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.75,0:19:49.59,Default,,0,0,0,,that it was inside\Nof you all along.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.95,0:19:53.40,Default,,0,0,0,,But telling ponies your tonic\Ncan do things it can't
Dialogue: 0,0:19:53.58,0:19:54.73,Default,,0,0,0,,is just wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.20,0:19:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But you just said it\Nboosts confidence!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:57.61,0:19:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's not all it\Ndoes, folks--
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.26,0:20:00.63,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Yes it is!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.71,0:20:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, it's not\Na tonic at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.22,0:20:06.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I know because I\Nhelped make it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.87,0:20:10.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Watching Applejack save Granny\Nand then admit to lying,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.77,0:20:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,well, that made me realize\NI was making ponies believe
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.11,0:20:16.20,Default,,0,0,0,,in a thing that\Njust wasn't so.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.68,0:20:19.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Believing in something can\Nhelp you do amazing things,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:19.56,0:20:21.51,Default,,0,0,0,,but if that belief\Nis based on a lie,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.07,0:20:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}eventually it's going to{\i0}\N{\i1}lead to real trouble.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:25.80,0:20:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Applejack.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.99,0:20:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,I got this through\Ndishonest means.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.38,0:20:33.28,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}That was a mistake I{\i0}\N{\i1}won't be making again.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.85,0:20:35.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd like you to have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.44,0:20:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,As a reminder of how you helped\Nme finally see the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.35,0:20:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.68,0:20:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.74,0:20:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll track down the pony I\Nsold that worthless tonic to
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.78,0:20:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and give them another bit\Nto replace this one.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.32,0:20:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Honest.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.18,0:20:51.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, Granny.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.84,0:20:53.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I hope this doesn't mean\Nyou'll stop swimming.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.91,0:20:56.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Why in tarnation\Nwould I do that?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.40,0:20:58.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I just can't believe\Nthose two salesponies
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.76,0:21:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,had me believing\NI could near fly.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.99,0:21:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, where'd they go?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:05.48,0:21:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Being honest sure gets hard{\i0}\N{\i1}when it seems like the truth{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:08.44,0:21:10.20,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}might hurt somepony{\i0}\N{\i1}you care about.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.52,0:21:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But I think believing a lie{\i0}\N{\i1}can end up hurting even more.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.31,0:21:16.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Maybe someponies don't{\i0}\N{\i1}care about that...{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.73,0:21:18.26,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}But I sure ain't one of them.{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.91,0:21:20.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you take it\Neasy, there, Granny.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.63,0:21:22.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, I plan to.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.73,0:21:24.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh. Ha, Whee!
